genres.name: Adventure
genres.description: A good adventure movie is the best way to escape from your usual life at least for a while and imagine yourself on board a spaceship or on a lonely raft in the endless ocean.

genres.name: Fantasy
genres.description: Situations, places and/or events that donâ€™t comply with natural laws or settings. They often involve some form of magic or supernatural elements. There are sometimes magical creatures or beings too.

genres.name: Horror
genres.description: The objective of a horror movie is to scare the viewer and if possible, make them scream (often done with a jump scare). Horror movies often feature a monster, some type of evil entity or a terrible/frightening situation.

genres.name: Action
genres.description: This type of movie generally involves a lot of action scenes including violence, like fighting or shoot-outs (with weapons), car chases and often lots of explosions. Some subgenres considered action movies include: disaster films, martial arts films, spy films and superhero films

genres.name: Comedy
genres.description: The main idea of comedies is to make the audience laugh. The main characters are involved in funny situations.

genres.name: Animated
genres.description: Instead of real actors on the screen, drawn images (nowadays computer generated ones) are used to tell the story. Real actors are used for the voices of the animated characters.
